A. Limited integration of new hardware components
B. Limited cabling required
C. Limited handling of large traffic
D. Built in a fashion which enables for easy integration of new hardware components
E. Limited installation and configuration process; D
Hybrid topology is easily scalable as it is built in a fashion which enables for easy integration of new hardware components.
Why is the installation and configuration of hybrid topology considered difficult?
A. Limited volume of traffic handling
B. Less expensive than other topologies
C. More expensive than other topologies
D. Less cabling required
E. Handles large volume of traffic; C
The installation and configuration of hybrid topology can be a difficult process, making it more expensive than other topologies.
What is a drawback of using hybrid topology in terms of cabling?
A. Less expensive than other topologies
B. Less hardware components required
C. Limited handling of large traffic
D. More cabling required
E. Limited scalability; D
A drawback of using hybrid topology is that more cabling is required compared to other topologies.
Arrange the functionalities given below to their respective layers:
A. divides packets into frames
B. at the sender divides the data received from the session layer into smaller units called segments
C. transmission of data from one host to the other located in different networks
D. adding headers (physical addresses MAC) to a frame to define sender or receiver; B
The functionality of dividing the data received from the session layer into smaller units called segments corresponds to the Transport Layer.
