How many layers does the TCP/IP reference model include?
A. Three layers: link, internet, and transport. 
B. Four layers: link, internet, transport, and application. 
C. Five layers: link, internet, transport, application, and physical. 
D. Seven layers: link, internet, transport, application, data link, network, and physical. 
E. Two layers: internet and application.; B
The TCP/IP reference model includes four layers: link, internet, transport, and application, with the physical layer not being specified.
