What is a semaphore used for in computer science?
A. Managing memory allocation
B. Synchronizing access to shared resources
C. Sorting algorithms
D. Error handling
E. Network communication; B
A semaphore is used to synchronize access to shared resources among multiple threads or processes. It is commonly used to prevent race conditions and coordinate the activities of concurrent processes.
Which of the following best describes the purpose of a semaphore?
A. Ensuring data integrity
B. Controlling access to databases
C. Managing network protocols
D. Facilitating inter-process communication
E. Optimizing CPU scheduling; D
Semaphores facilitate inter-process communication by allowing processes to signal and wait for each other, thereby coordinating their activities and preventing conflicts when accessing shared resources.
In a multiprogramming system, what is the issue called when two or more processes waiting for a shared resource may never get the resource at all and will be waiting indefinitely?
