Which of the following is a necessary condition for a system to be considered deadlocked?
A. Shareable resource currently being held by a process. 
B. Mutual Exclusion. 
C. Resources can be forcibly removed from a process. 
D. Process waiting for resources in a circular manner. 
E. Non-preemption.; D
The condition of a process waiting for resources in a circular manner is known as circular wait, which is one of the necessary conditions for a system to be considered deadlocked.
What does the 'Hold and wait' condition refer to in the context of deadlock?
A. Resources can be forcibly removed from a process. 
B. Processes holding resources and waiting for other resources. 
C. Non-shareable resource currently being held by a process. 
D. Process waiting for resources in a circular manner. 
E. Non-preemption.; B
The 'Hold and wait' condition refers to processes in the system holding resources and waiting for other resources, which is a necessary condition for deadlock.
Which condition ensures that a process cannot forcibly remove resources from another process?
A. Mutual Exclusion. 
B. Non-preemption. 
C. Shareable resource currently being held by a process. 
D. Process waiting for resources in a circular manner. 
E. Processes holding resources and waiting for other resources.; B
The condition of non-preemption ensures that resources cannot be forcibly removed from a process and can only be voluntarily released.
What is the purpose of Remote Procedure Calls (RPC)?
A. To overcome the disadvantage of message passing using system call send and receive. 
B. To enhance message passing using system call send and receive. 
C. To replace message passing using system call send and receive. 
D. To complicate message passing using system call send and receive. 
E. To ignore message passing using system call send and receive.; A
The purpose of Remote Procedure Calls (RPC) is to overcome the disadvantage of message passing using system call send and receive, allowing communication between processes running on different systems as though they were running on the local system.
What is the first step when a process in machine A calls a procedure in the remote machine B?
A. The client stub converts the procedure call to a message by extracting the parameters and sends it to machine B using the system call send. 
B. The message reaches machine B's operating system and is forwarded to the server stub. 
C. The client stub calls receive and remains in a blocked state until receiving a response from machine B. 
D. The request is first sent to a process called the client stub. 
E. The server stub converts the message to a procedure call, calling the appropriate procedure in the local system (machine B).; D
The first step when a process in machine A calls a procedure in the remote machine B is that the request is first sent to a process called the client stub, as mentioned in the content.
What is the role of the client stub in the remote procedure call process?
A. It forwards the message to the server stub. 
B. It converts the message to a procedure call and calls the appropriate procedure in the local system (machine B). 
C. It remains in a blocked state until receiving a response from machine B. 
D. It converts the procedure call to a message by extracting the parameters and sends it to machine B using the system call send. 
E. It executes the procedure and converts the result to a message to be sent to machine A using the send system call.; D
The role of the client stub in the remote procedure call process is to convert the procedure call to a message by extracting the parameters and sends it to machine B using the system call send, as mentioned in the content.
What happens when the message reaches machine B in the remote procedure call process?
A. The client stub converts the procedure call to a message and sends it to machine B using the system call send. 
B. The message is forwarded to the server stub. 
C. The client stub calls receive and remains in a blocked state until receiving a response from machine B. 
D. The request is first sent to a process called the client stub. 
E. The server stub converts the message to a procedure call, calling the appropriate procedure in the local system (machine B).; B
When the message reaches machine B in the remote procedure call process, the machine B's operating system forwards the message to the server stub, as mentioned in the content.
What is the purpose of the server stub in Remote Procedure Calls (RPC)?
A. To forward messages to the client
B. To make the receive system call and wait for a message from the client
C. To block the client from receiving the result
D. To handle network messages
E. To leave the blocked state; B
The server stub makes the receive system call and is in a blocked state until it receives a message back from the client, so option B is correct.
What happens when the message (result) reaches machine A in Remote Procedure Calls (RPC)?
A. The message is discarded
B. The operating system forwards it to the server stub
C. The client stub remains in a blocked state
D. The message is sent back to the client
E. The client stub receives the result and forwards it to the calling process; E
Once the message (result) reaches machine A, the operating system forwards it to the client stub, which can then leave its blocked state and forwards the result to the calling process, making option E correct.
